.\" termin.al-name: tail
.\" termin.al-usage: tail [-n count] [path]
.\" termin.al-summary: Print final raw document lines.
.TH TAIL 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
tail \- Print final raw document lines.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
tail [-n count] [path]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads piped text when no path is supplied; otherwise reads one virtual document as raw text. Prints the final newline-separated lines. Paths resolve relative to the current pane directory or from virtual home with
.BR ~ .
The default count is 10.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -n count
Select a non-negative decimal line count from 0 through 1000. The option may precede or follow a path operand; a later
.B -n
replaces an earlier count.
.SH OUTPUT
Markdown is not rendered. A count of 0 emits an empty text output; a count larger than the document returns all available text lines. A trailing newline is preserved by the raw split-and-join behavior.
.SH FAILURES
Unsupported options, a missing or invalid count, more than one path, no path outside a pipeline, invalid or missing paths, directories, locked files and unavailable documents are rejected. Cancellation returns no output.
.SH LIMITS
The requested count is capped at 1000 lines.
.SH NOTES
The command reads published or redirected virtual-file text and accepts no host filesystem path.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ cat about.md | tail -n 3
$ tail about.md
$ tail -n 3 ~/changelog.md
$ tail about.md -n 0
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
head(1), cat(1), less(1)
